1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:09,041
[Chorus]

2
00:00:09,191 --> 00:00:13,233
The importance of bearing witness—

3
00:00:13,383 --> 00:00:17,424
To show you saw, to say you knew.

4
00:00:17,574 --> 00:00:21,615
To hold the silence, speak the truth,

5
00:00:21,765 --> 00:00:25,807
Even when the wind blows cruel.

6
00:00:25,957 --> 00:00:29,998
The importance of bearing witness.

7
00:00:30,148 --> 00:00:34,190
[Verse 1]

8
00:00:34,340 --> 00:00:38,381
To watch and not look away,

9
00:00:38,531 --> 00:00:42,572
To say, “I was there,”

10
00:00:42,722 --> 00:00:46,764
To hold a story that’s not your own

11
00:00:46,914 --> 00:00:50,955
Like it matters that you care.

12
00:00:51,105 --> 00:00:55,146
To see the cracks and name them plain,

13
00:00:55,296 --> 00:00:59,338
To know it’s not just someone else’s pain.

14
00:00:59,488 --> 00:01:03,529
[Chorus]

15
00:01:03,679 --> 00:01:07,721
Bearing witness—it matters so.

16
00:01:07,871 --> 00:01:11,912
Like rain that helps the wildflowers grow.

17
00:01:12,062 --> 00:01:16,103
A record kept in soul, not stone,

18
00:01:16,253 --> 00:01:20,295
So no one has to stand alone.

19
00:01:20,445 --> 00:01:24,486
Bearing witness—it matters so.

20
00:01:24,636 --> 00:01:28,677
[Verse 2]

21
00:01:28,827 --> 00:01:32,869
To listen when it’s hard to hear,

22
00:01:33,019 --> 00:01:37,060
To sit with truth, even smeared in fear.

23
00:01:37,210 --> 00:01:41,252
To lift a voice that’s growing faint,

24
00:01:41,402 --> 00:01:45,443
To stand, not as a saint,

25
00:01:45,593 --> 00:01:49,634
But as someone who chose to stay.

26
00:01:49,784 --> 00:01:53,826
Just stayed. And heard. And didn’t look
away.

27
00:01:53,976 --> 00:01:58,017
[Chorus]

28
00:01:58,167 --> 00:02:02,208
The importance of bearing witness—

29
00:02:02,358 --> 00:02:06,400
To echo cries that fade too fast.

30
00:02:06,550 --> 00:02:10,591
To make a moment hold and last,

31
00:02:10,741 --> 00:02:14,783
To be the mirror, not the mask.

32
00:02:14,933 --> 00:02:18,974
The importance of bearing witness.

33
00:02:19,124 --> 00:02:23,165
[Verse 3]

34
00:02:23,315 --> 00:02:27,357
To carry weight that’s not your own,

35
00:02:27,507 --> 00:02:31,548
To say, “I saw what had been shown.”

36
00:02:31,698 --> 00:02:35,739
Not to fix, or shine, or save—

37
00:02:35,889 --> 00:02:39,931
Just to walk beside the brave.

38
00:02:40,081 --> 00:02:44,122
To show the wound, not just the scar.

39
00:02:44,272 --> 00:02:48,314
To say, “I know who you are.”

40
00:02:48,464 --> 00:02:52,505
[Chorus]

41
00:02:52,655 --> 00:02:56,696
Bearing witness, it’s a vow—

42
00:02:56,846 --> 00:03:00,888
To mark the then, to name the now.

43
00:03:01,038 --> 00:03:05,079
So future hands can hold the thread,

44
00:03:05,229 --> 00:03:09,270
Of what was done, what should be said.

45
00:03:09,420 --> 00:03:13,462
Bearing witness, it’s a vow.

46
00:03:13,612 --> 00:03:17,653
[Outro]

47
00:03:17,803 --> 00:03:21,845
A whisper in the dark, a light dim but
true—

48
00:03:21,995 --> 00:03:26,036
A thread between the me and you.

49
00:03:26,186 --> 00:03:30,227
Stories caught and passed like flame,

50
00:03:30,377 --> 00:03:34,419
So no one ever forgets the name.

51
00:03:34,569 --> 00:03:38,610
That’s the importance of bearing witness.
